 yang]]. The Sun, Moon and blue colour represent the [[Tengri|eternal sky]] |- |{{flagicon|Tajikistan}} |[[Tajikistan]] ([[Flag of Tajikistan|flag]]) |The seven stars representing number seven in [[Persian mythology|Tajik traditional legends]], representing perfection and happiness while alluding to a traditional belief that the heavens feature seven mountains and seven orchard gardens with a star shining above each mountain. |- |{{flagicon|Uruguay}} |[[Uruguay]] ([[Flag of Uruguay|flag]]) |[[Sun of May]]'s features are that of the [[Inca]] god [[Inti]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.all-flags-world.com/country-flag/flag-uruguay.php |title=Flag of Uruguay |publisher=All-flags-world.com |date= |accessdate=2014-02-02}}</ref> |}
